So here's been my observations on Burgeoning/Exploration; both seem way better than they really are most of the time, and that's doubly true in a deck where your commander and other things already give you extra land drops

Occasionally you'll get a bursty turn 1/2 and hit draw right away to refill, but way way more often you'll play your lands, empty your hand, and be in topdeck mode by turn 4, basically being in the same position as everyoen else while drawing a bunch of attention
There's decks they work. I love both in Edric where I'm drawing all the cards, but you're drawing less and already have ways to play extra lands in the command zone

I feel the same way, actually. I can see a good reason to cut Burgeoning. Exploration is nice here with Crucible/Ramunap, but Burgeoning has gotten stale before. I wouldn't put them in other decks. Alham's Archive being described as "cute" is probably the exact right diagnosis
Burgeoning can with with the Dryad/Path of discovery where you have a fair chance to get a land across several upkeep’s to keep your hand full, but that’s a lot of moving parts.
